defmodule Solution do
  @spec count_pairs(coordinates :: [[integer]], k :: integer) :: integer
  def count_pairs(coordinates, k) do
    coordinates
    |> Enum.with_index()
    |> Enum.reduce(0, fn {coord1, i1}, acc ->
      acc + Enum.count(Enum.slice(coordinates, i1 + 1..-1), fn coord2 ->
        distance(coord1, coord2) == k
      end)
    end)
  end

  defp distance([x1, y1], [x2, y2]), do: Bitwise.bxor(x1, x2) + Bitwise.bxor(y1, y2)
end
